{"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Initializer","fragments":[{"text":"init","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"unix"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:4GLib9IOChannelC4unixACSi_tcfc","title":"init(unix:)","symbolKind":"init"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel\/init(unix:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Creates a new "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel"},{"text":" given a file descriptor. On UNIX systems","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"this works for plain files, pipes, and sockets.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/iochannel\/init(unix:)"]}],"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"init"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"unix","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"fd"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The returned "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" has a reference count of 1."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The default encoding for ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel","isActive":true},{"text":" is UTF-8. If your application","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is reading output from a command using via pipe, you may need to set"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the encoding to the encoding of the current locale (see"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_get_charset()"},{"type":"text","text":") with the "},{"code":"g_io_channel_set_encoding()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"By default, the fd passed will not be closed when the final reference","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" data structure is dropped."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you want to read raw binary data without interpretation, then","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"call the "},{"code":"g_io_channel_set_encoding()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function with ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"encoding argument."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function is available in GLib on Windows, too, but you should"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"avoid using it on Windows. The domain of file descriptors and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"sockets overlap. There is no way for GLib to know which one you mean","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"in case the argument you pass to this function happens to be both a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"valid file descriptor and socket. If that happens a warning is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"issued, and GLib assumes that it is the file descriptor you mean.","type":"text"}]}]}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContext":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MainContext"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontext","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GMainContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" struct is an opaque data"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"type representing a set of sources to be handled in a main loop.","type":"text"}],"title":"MainContext","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"abstract":[],"kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/glib","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/IOChannel":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"GIOChannel","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" data type aims to provide a portable method for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"using file descriptors, pipes, and sockets, and integrating them"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"into the main event loop (see [struct","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext"},{"type":"text","text":"]). Currently,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"full support is available on UNIX platforms; support for Windows"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is only partially complete.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"IOChannel","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"IOChannel","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"IOChannel"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/iochannel"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/IOChannel/init(unix:)":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/iochannel\/init(unix:)","title":"init(unix:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel\/init(unix:)","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"init"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"unix"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Creates a new "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" given a file descriptor. On UNIX systems","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"this works for plain files, pipes, and sockets.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","role":"symbol"}}}